courses.description: Introduction to drawing materials and techniques with an emphasis on observation, representation, and formal principles of composition and design.
Prerequisite: 3400:210. Lecture course providing appreciation and understanding of various types/periods with emphasis on topics and infl uences on societies, rather than on historical sequences.

courses.course_title: Photography I For Non- Art Majors
courses.description: A study of photography through lecture, demonstration and studio work. An exploration and enrichment opportunity for the non-art major. No credit toward a major in art.
Prerequisite: 7100:131 and 144, or 286 or 2240:124. Lecture, studio and laboratory course techniques and aesthetics are studied using 35mm cameras. A 35mm camera with full manual control is required.
